Malaysia’s Employer EPF Payments to Rise to 13% for Low Earners

-- B y   E l f f i e   C h e w   a n d   C h o n g   P o o i   K o o n
-- 
2011-10-07T09:53:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-07/malaysia-s-employer-epf-payments-to-rise-to-13-for-low-earners.html
Employers in  Malaysia  will have to
increase their payments to the Employees Provident Fund to 13
percent of workers’ salaries, Prime Minister Najib Razak said in
his budget speech in parliament in  Kuala Lumpur  today.  That’s up from 12 percent and applies to individuals
earning 5,000 ringgit a month or less, he said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Elffie Chew at 
 echew16@bloomberg.net  